{q:"What is the meaning of the final sentence?", opts:["Foxes recently invaded human cities","Humans built their homes on land foxes already lived on","Foxes and humans arrived at the same time","Foxes prefer the countryside to towns"], a:1, ex:"Foxes 'were using these hills and hollows long before the streets were laid' — so really humans moved into fox territory."}
